The ack_vack module
===================

	>>> import ack_vack
	>>> print ack_vack.__doc__
	Script to change -v for an ack command to vack

More modules for testing
------------------------
	>>> import shlex

Test main
---------

Convenience method
	>>> def test_main(string):
	...     ack_vack.main(shlex.split(string))

ack should be added to arguments
	>>> test_main('stuff')
	ack stuff

'-v' should change that to vack
	>>> test_main('stuff -v')
	vack stuff

	>>> test_main('-v stuff ')
	vack stuff

Quotes should be preserved
	>>> test_main('stuff "and nonsense"')
	ack stuff "and nonsense"

Except that bash would have stripped the actual quotation marks away
	so we can only guess, and prefer double quotes
	>>> test_main("stuff 'and nonsense'")
	ack stuff "and nonsense"

If there's a dollar in it then single quotes must have been used
	>>> test_main("stuff 'and $nonsense'")
	ack stuff 'and $nonsense'

Combination of -v and quotes
	>>> test_main('stuff -v "and nonsense"')
	vack stuff "and nonsense"

Other options should pass through
	>>> test_main('stuff -w "and nonsense"')
	ack stuff -w "and nonsense"
	>>> test_main('stuff -v -w "and nonsense"')
	vack stuff -w "and nonsense"
	>>> test_main('stuff -vw "and nonsense"')
	vack stuff -w "and nonsense"
	>>> test_main('stuff -wv "and nonsense"')
	vack stuff -w "and nonsense"
	>>> test_main('stuff -iwv "and nonsense"')
	vack stuff -iw "and nonsense"
	>>> test_main('stuff -ivw "and nonsense"')
	vack stuff -iw "and nonsense"
	>>> test_main('stuff -viw "and nonsense"')
	vack stuff -iw "and nonsense"
